title: Econometrics by Example
description:
Econometrics by Example

English | Apr. 15, 2011 | ISBN: 0230290396 | 320 Pages | PDF | 18.89 MB


Damodar Gujarati is the author of bestselling econometrics textbooks used around the world. In his latest book, Econometrics by Example, Gujarati presents a unique learning-by-doing approach to the study of econometrics. Rather than relying on complex theoretical discussions and complicated mathematics, this book explains econometrics from a practical point of view, with each chapter anchored in one or two extended real-life examples
